WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.549
Open Settings, and find the Locations group in the left rail.

p02
00:00:03.879 --> 00:00:05.244
Four pages live here.

p03
00:00:05.606 --> 00:00:09.041
One holds every site you run and everything hanging off it.

p04
00:00:09.435 --> 00:00:14.428
The other three group your sites, style what customers see, and guard the payment keys.

p05
00:00:14.712 --> 00:00:17.358
We'll read all four, and change none of them.

p06
00:00:17.760 --> 00:00:19.434
Now open Locations.

p07
00:00:20.091 --> 00:00:22.686
A band of tiles reads the network at a glance: how many sites, how many active,

p08
00:00:23.004 --> 00:00:27.452
how many states, and when they last synced.

p09
00:00:27.934 --> 00:00:28.354
Under it, three panels chart growth, split the sites by state,

p10
00:00:28.642 --> 00:00:30.108
and score how healthy their setup is.

p11
00:00:30.407 --> 00:00:34.046
This is your map before you open a single site.

p12
00:00:34.547 --> 00:00:37.302
And if the list underneath ever reads couldn't load,

p13
00:00:37.803 --> 00:00:43.911
that's the agent service dropping, not an empty tenant.

p14
00:00:44.496 --> 00:00:46.313
Look at the list itself.

p15
00:00:46.313 --> 00:00:49.074
Eight columns, and the one that matters most is Code.

p16
00:00:49.074 --> 00:00:53.152
That short site code follows a location through every screen in the platform,

p17
00:00:53.152 --> 00:00:54.808
so learn to read it first.

p18
00:00:54.808 --> 00:00:59.757
Search by name or code up top, filter beside it, and leave New Record alone.

p19
00:00:59.757 --> 00:01:03.759
Last Sync on the right tells you when the site last checked in,

p20
00:01:03.759 --> 00:01:07.071
which is the first thing you read when a site looks silent.

p21
00:01:07.520 --> 00:01:08.865
Click a site to open it.

p22
00:01:10.172 --> 00:01:12.040
One location, five tabs.

p23
00:01:12.432 --> 00:01:14.152
Profile, Operations, Payments and Credentials, Messaging, and Users.

p24
00:01:14.387 --> 00:01:15.592
That strip is the whole record,

p25
00:01:15.808 --> 00:01:17.379
and every support question about a site starts by picking the right tab.

p26
00:01:17.840 --> 00:01:25.990
Profile is where you land.

p27
00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:27.961
Start with Profile.

p28
00:01:28.424 --> 00:01:30.065
This is who and where: the site's code and name, its address, its contact details, its hours.

p29
00:01:30.311 --> 00:01:34.909
When a ticket names a location you don't recognize,

p30
00:01:35.544 --> 00:01:42.880
this tab confirms you're looking at the right one before you touch anything else.

p31
00:01:43.280 --> 00:01:43.965
Now Operations.

p32
00:01:43.965 --> 00:01:47.983
This tab runs the site's behavior and its time clock.

p33
00:01:47.983 --> 00:01:51.991
Whether it shows on dashboards, whether it takes online orders,

p34
00:01:51.991 --> 00:01:56.154
and the rules that clock staff out and pay overtime.

p35
00:01:56.154 --> 00:01:59.237
Find the automatic clock-out timeout and the overtime threshold,

p36
00:01:59.237 --> 00:02:02.320
read them, and leave them exactly as they are.

p37
00:02:02.720 --> 00:02:04.564
Open Payments and Credentials.

p38
00:02:05.528 --> 00:02:13.101
Below the portal and auto-charge options sits Credential Configuration,

p39
00:02:13.572 --> 00:02:14.226
split into a block for each processor a site can run:

p40
00:02:14.561 --> 00:02:15.282
Open Edge, Smart Tech, Other, and Card Connect.

p41
00:02:15.724 --> 00:02:17.402
Every secret shows masked.

p42
00:02:18.351 --> 00:02:20.012
Your job is to name which block is present, never to read the value.

p43
00:02:20.293 --> 00:02:28.640
For a decline ticket, the gateway name is all support needs.

p44
00:02:29.114 --> 00:02:30.086
Two tabs left. Messaging.

p45
00:02:30.625 --> 00:02:31.364
This holds the messages a site sends on its own, set per location rather than network-wide.

p46
00:02:31.854 --> 00:02:42.454
When a customer at one site gets a text that another site's customers don't, this tab is why.

p47
00:02:42.718 --> 00:02:45.152
You read what's set here; you send nothing.

p48
00:02:45.600 --> 00:02:46.905
Then Users.

p49
00:02:47.442 --> 00:02:49.050
This is who can work this site.

p50
00:02:49.597 --> 00:02:54.105
When someone says they can't get into a location, check here before you reset anything:

p51
00:02:54.416 --> 00:02:56.387
they may simply not be assigned to it.

p52
00:02:56.838 --> 00:02:58.880
Read the list; open nothing.

p53
00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:00.764
Back out with the Back button.

p54
00:03:01.324 --> 00:03:03.269
Nothing saved, nothing changed.

p55
00:03:03.832 --> 00:03:07.737
And even if you wanted to swap a site's credentials, you couldn't finish it here:

p56
00:03:08.227 --> 00:03:12.160
those changes route to an approval queue, which is the next page we read.

p57
00:03:12.640 --> 00:03:14.302
Open Location Groups.

p58
00:03:15.506 --> 00:03:20.176
A group bundles several sites so a report or a dashboard treats them as one.

p59
00:03:20.837 --> 00:03:21.709
Five columns: the name, a description, how many sites it holds,

p60
00:03:22.016 --> 00:03:26.115
its geo group, and whether it shows on the dashboard.

p61
00:03:26.444 --> 00:03:29.085
Read only.

p62
00:03:29.577 --> 00:03:31.699
Next, Location Sub-Brand.

p63
00:03:32.456 --> 00:03:33.799
The link says Sub-Brand, the page says Sub-Brands, same place.

p64
00:03:34.045 --> 00:03:36.745
This styles the customer-facing panels, the panel type and the colors,

p65
00:03:37.405 --> 00:03:44.837
so one operator can run sites under more than one look.

p66
00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:46.102
Last page: Payment Credential Approval.

p67
00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:47.939
This is where those credential changes land for sign-off.

p68
00:03:48.414 --> 00:03:50.871
Each row shows a location, its gateway, and a status: pending, approved, or rejected.

p69
00:03:51.505 --> 00:03:55.010
In the capture, two sites sat approved on Open Edge.

p70
00:03:55.363 --> 00:03:57.416
When an admin says a site's new keys aren't live yet, this status column is your answer,

p71
00:03:58.049 --> 00:04:09.440
one pending row and you know it's still in the queue.

p72
00:04:09.840 --> 00:04:11.580
So that's the Locations area.

p73
00:04:11.968 --> 00:04:14.243
One list, one five-tab record, three sibling pages.

p74
00:04:14.492 --> 00:04:15.823
The site list gets you in,

p75
00:04:16.030 --> 00:04:17.786
the tabs tell you who, how, and with which processor,

p76
00:04:18.011 --> 00:04:26.192
and the sibling pages bundle sites, style them, and sign off their credentials.

p77
00:04:26.619 --> 00:04:29.439
You read all of it, and you change none of it.

